# üé® Coding Style

## Function Declarations
- Always use arrow functions for components and functions
- Use `const` by default; use `let` only when needed
- Always use `export default` for all exports (components, hooks, utilities, etc.)

## Control Flow
- Always use block statements with curly braces
- Avoid single-line control flow statements
- Examples:
  ```typescript
  // ‚ùå Avoid
  if (condition) return null;
  if (condition) continue;
  if (condition) break;
  
  // ‚úÖ Prefer
  if (condition) {
    return null;
  }
  
  if (condition) {
    continue;
  }
  
  if (condition) {
    break;
  }
  ```

## Naming Conventions
- React Components: PascalCase (e.g., `Button.tsx`, `UserProfile.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase (e.g., `useAuth.ts`, `useForm.ts`)
- Utilities/Stores: kebab-case (e.g., `auth-store.ts`, `format-date.ts`)
